---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import BreadcrumbSchema from '../components/schema/BreadcrumbSchema.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Percolate privacy policy, what data we collect, how it is used, and how to delete your account."
  path="/privacy"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <BreadcrumbSchema crumbs={[{ name: 'Privacy Policy', url: `${SITE.url}/privacy` }]} />
  </Fragment>

  <p class="brand">{SITE.name}</p>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="effective">Effective Date: May 13, 2026</p>

  <p>
    Percolate ("we", "our", or "the app") is a coffee shelf and
    cupping-log app for iOS, with a companion website at
    <a href={SITE.url}>{SITE.url}</a>. This policy explains what we collect,
    how we use it, and how to delete it, for both the app and the website.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>Account information.</strong> If you sign in with Apple or Google,
    we receive your email and a unique identifier from the provider. Guest
    accounts store only an anonymous identifier with no personal information.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>User-generated content.</strong> Shelf entries, cupping logs,
    ratings, flavor-quiz responses, taste-profile data, private notes,
    and community posts are stored in your account.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Device data.</strong> A device identifier and basic diagnostics
    (OS version, device model, app version) are collected to deliver core
    features and prevent abuse. We do not collect precise location.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Purchases.</strong> Percolate is free and does not sell anything
    in-app, so we do not process payments or collect payment details. When you
    follow a &ldquo;Buy from&rdquo; link to a roaster, your purchase is made on
    their site under their own terms.
  </p>

  <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To run your shelf, cupping log, and taste profile.</li>
    <li>To suggest coffees you already own based on roast, origin, process, and recent cups.</li>
    <li>To sync your shelf and cupping history across devices.</li>
    <li>To improve our taste-profile model using anonymized quiz and cupping data.</li>
    <li>To connect you to roasters through outbound &ldquo;Buy from&rdquo; links.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Privacy Posture</h2>
  <p>
    Your shelf, cupping log, ratings, private notes, and taste profile are
    <strong>private by default</strong>. A rating becomes part of the community
    average only when you explicitly choose to publish it. We do not run
    cross-user advertising, and we do not sell personal information.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>
    We rely on the following third parties to operate the app. Each receives
    only the data necessary for the service it provides:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Supabase</strong>, backend storage and authentication.</li>
    <li><strong>Apple / Google</strong>, sign-in.</li>
    <li><strong>PostHog</strong>, anonymous usage analytics.</li>
    <li><strong>Sentry</strong>, anonymous crash reporting.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Affiliate Link Tracking</h2>
  <p>
    When a coffee detail page links out to a roaster or specialty retailer,
    that site may set cookies or identifiers on the destination page that we
    have no control over. Percolate itself only records that an outbound click
    occurred, we do not pass your account identity to the roaster or
    retailer.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
  <p>
    Your data is retained as long as your account is active. You may delete
    your account at any time from the Profile screen, which permanently
    removes all associated data including shelf entries, cupping logs,
    flavor-quiz history, taste profile, ratings, private notes, and community
    posts.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
  <p>
    You may request a copy of your data, request correction or deletion, and
    withdraw consent at any time. California residents and EU users have
    additional rights under CCPA and GDPR respectively. Contact us using the
    address below.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    Percolate is not directed to children under 13. We do not knowingly
    collect information from anyone under 13.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Data Security</h2>
  <p>
    All data is transmitted over HTTPS and stored in secured, access-controlled
    databases. Authentication tokens are stored securely on your device. We
    follow industry-standard practices to protect your information.
  </p>

  <h2>10. How to Delete Your Account</h2>
  <p>You may delete your account in two ways:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>In-app:</strong> Profile &rarr; Settings &rarr; Delete Account.</li>
    <li><strong>By email:</strong> if you cannot access the app, email
      <a href={`mailto:${SITE.supportEmail}`}>{SITE.supportEmail}</a> from
      your account email with the subject <strong>"Delete My Account"</strong>.
      We will permanently remove your account within 7 days.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy from time to time. Material changes will be
    communicated through the app. Continued use after changes constitutes
    acceptance.
  </p>

  <h2>12. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    For questions about this privacy policy or your data, contact us at:
    <a href={`mailto:${SITE.supportEmail}`}>{SITE.supportEmail}</a>
  </p>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
